My meme

My meme is based on the different Kevin Hart reactions that are trending right now and relates to a little bit about two NBA players, one from my favourite team the Dallas Mavericks.

library(magick)

# Reading in the first image for the meme
first_image <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FqCwvspXoAEjZsk?format=jpg&name=small") %>%
  image_scale(300)
# Creating the first text square and annotating it
first_text <- image_blank(width = 270,
                          height = 200,
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Seeing Luka Doncic blow a 27 point lead",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 15,
                 gravity = "center")
# concatenating the first text and image
first_row_vector <- c(first_text, first_image)

# appending these two squares side by side
first_row <- image_append(first_row_vector)

# reading in the second image for the meme
second_image <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/002/542/258/747.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# creating a second text square and annotating it
second_text <- image_blank(width = 270,
                           height = 260,
                           color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Jayson Tatum blows a 28 point lead \n 3 days later",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 15,
                 gravity = "center")

# concatenating the second text and image
second_row_vector <- c(second_text, second_image)

# appending the second text square and second image side by side
second_row <- image_append(second_row_vector)

# concatenating the first and second rows
full_meme_vector <- c(first_row, second_row)

# appending the first and second rows of the meme on top of each other
full_meme <- image_append(full_meme_vector, stack = TRUE)

# displaying the meme and creating a png of it
full_meme %>% image_write("full_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My Animated GIF is inspired very non creatively by a sequence of chess moves called the Scholars Mate, that catch out not very experienced players into a swift checkmate.

library(magick)

# reading in the 8 frames
frame1 <- image_read("blank.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame2 <- image_read("e4.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame3 <- image_read("e5.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame4 <- image_read("Bc4.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame5 <- image_read("Nc6.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame6 <- image_read("Qh4.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame7 <- image_read("Bc5.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)
frame8 <- image_read("Qxf7#.jpg") %>% image_scale(400)

# concatenating the 8 frames.
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6, frame7, frame8)

# adding a fading in and out transition and animating the frames.
image_morph(frames) %>% image_animate(fps = 5, loop = 1)

# creating a .gif of my animation
image_write(frames, "full_animation.gif")
